HEADWORD: Rhabdom
<hw>Rhab"dom</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧b"d⟦ocr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ra`bdwma</grk> a bundle of rods, fr. <grk>"ra`bdos</grk> a
rod.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of numerous minute rodlike
structures formed of two or more cells situated behind the retinulae in
the compound eyes of insects, etc. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Ommatidium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

